1. Classical prefix sum problem, but it requires attention if a few small details
2. Create prefix and suffix sum arrays and FILL THEM WITH NONES to be able to work with their indexes
3. When you're filling the suffix sum array, don't forget to go BACKWARDS!
4. Pay attention, that if you didn't find pivot index, you need to return -1 (not 0!)
5. DON'T FORGET TO RETURN THE FIRST PIVOT INDEX, THAT YOU'VE MET! According to task's condition, you have to return
the leftmost pivot index you found, but if you forget to break the cycle, you would rewrite the answer if there are many